### Tier mapping

| Pressure Change     | Card Label      | Card Line         | Overlay Interpretation                                                 |
| ------------------- | --------------- | ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Steady**          | Steady          | → Steady          | Stable pressure suggests settled weather conditions.                   |
| **Rising**          | Rising          | ↗ Rising          | Rising pressure often brings improving weather.                        |
| **Rising quickly**  | Rising quickly  | ↗ Rising quickly  | Rapidly rising pressure suggests clearing skies and calmer conditions. |
| **Falling**         | Falling         | ↘ Falling         | Falling pressure may signal unsettled weather.                         |
| **Falling quickly** | Falling quickly | ↘ Falling quickly | Rapid pressure drops often precede unsettled or stormy conditions.     |

